{"id":"322233213_Cosine_similarity_and_the_Borda_rule","abstract":"Cosine similarity is a commonly used similarity measure in computer science. We apply this similarity measure to define a voting rule, namely, the cosine similarity rule. This rule selects a social ranking that maximizes cosine similarity between the social ranking and a given preference profile. Our main finding is that the cosine similarity rule in fact coincides with the Borda rule.","authors":["Yoko Kawada"],"meta":["June 2018Social Choice and Welfare 51(1)","DOI:10.1007/s00355-017-1104-2"],"references":["332352881_The_Borda_rule_and_the_pairwise-majority-loser_revisited","276275820_'A_Geometric_Examination_of_Kemeny's_Rule","313522102_A_consistent_extension_of_Condorcet's_election_principle","306218220_Modern_information_retrieval_A_brief_overview_IEEE_Data_Eng","292766142_Modern_Information_Retrieval_A_Brief_Overview","276275927_Mathematics_Without_Numbers","276275613_Essai_sur_l'Application_de_L'Analyse_a_la_Probabilite_des_Decisions_Rendues_a_la_Pluraliste_des_Voix_Paris","276275611_Memoire_sur_les_Elections_au_Scrutin","248066135_Partial_Justification_of_the_Borda_Count","245764909_Condorcet''s_Theory_of_Voting","244953812_A_Consistent_Extension_of_Condorcet's_Election_Principle","226849974_Borda's_Rule_Positional_Voting_and_Condorcet's_Simple_Majority_Principle","222257404_Consistency_without_neutrality_in_voting_rules_When_is_a_vote_an_average","222172386_A_Dictionary_for_Voting_Paradoxes","220812245_Preference_Functions_That_Score_Rankings_and_Maximum_Likelihood_Estimation"]}